title: Grateful Dead Live at Rainbow Theatre on 1981-03-20
description: Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, CC Rider, Althea, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loser, Minglewood Blues, Candyman-> Looks Like Rain-> Deal Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Great Songs There are some great songs with great variety, but the quality is low. I like the way the songs are done though.
Meh Warm up show, no highlights.

Good show.    Maybe not the best show, or full of legendary versions of songs, but a perfectly good show. Despite some other reviews here, i think there are some highlights: Truckin is above average with lot's of energy, and Wharf Rat is pretty good too. He's Gone is almost always good and this one doesn't disappoint, but the vocal jam and instrumental jam are short and there are certainly better examples out there.
